{
  "stem": "935.8",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He looked like a teddy bear.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He was looking for people, prisoners, who were gutsy enough or stupid enough to find out, through a set up network in the camp itself, who was really in the camp on political prisoners, on high political prisoners, like de Gaulle and some of the de Gaulle click.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He got to this buddy of mine-- to Eva and me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he checked us out very carefully before he dared to come to us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And Eva was from Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And Ravensbruck had an awful lot of Czechs there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they hated the Germans with a wonderful passion.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I mean, really.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And they went all out, trying to find out as much as they could.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "A lot of them worked in offices and things like this, so they had access to a lot of information.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was not because they were worried about us, but for the names of the Germans who were running around in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we were first in one cell.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was an underground bunker, right outside Ravensbruck, which we had heard existed, but didn't know.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had also heard, which was true, that when the first assassination of Hitler took place, which, unfortunately, didn't work, these officers were sitting in that bunker in Ravensbruck.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So were all the big politicians from my city, Vienna.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Karl Seitz, the mayor of Vienna, the democratic mayor.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "A lot of them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "From Leipzig, there was the mayor of Leipzig.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "These political people were all sitting in Ravensbruck.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I think the reason was probably because it was so close to Berlin and it was supposed to be held anyway until the bitter end.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So they weren't worried about us, but about the names, which we had in the German underground, which was working.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
